    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <head>No. 505.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Schuyler</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 15, 1875</date>.
                            (Received June 3.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 116.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that a treaty
                        has been concluded between Russia and Japan, by which Russia cedes to Japan
                        the Kurile <pb facs="0412" n="1066" xml:id="pg_1066"/> Islands, in exchange
                        for all the rights of Japan to the island of Saghalien.]</p>
                <p>I understand that the treaty has already been ratified by the Emperor of
                        Russia.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EUGENE SCHUYLER.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
